.SS "HTML Production"
The HTML built is slightly easier as \fBidc\fR generates a single
.Ht htp 4
file which is compiled using
.Ht htmlc 1
generating a single
.Ht hts 4
file which may be expanded using
.Ht hts2html 1 .
The Makefile fragment is defined as follows:
.CS
buglist.hts: $(BUGS) $(IDC) buglist.rsp
        $(IDC) -H jasspa -h -o $@ -e idchtml.err SF=0 @buglist.rsp
        $(HTMLC) -v 1 -s buglist -o $@ buglist.htp
        $(RM) buglist.htp
.CE 0
.SH NOTES
Release 2.2.0 of the \fBidc\fR compiler introduced the in-line text formatting
constructs as defined by 
.Hl idc(4) idcFormat 4 .
The \fBBase Address:\fR  construct was removed and the  \fBftp:\fR/\fBeftp:\fR
group construct was removed and replaced with the in-line \fBftp:\fR function,
the \fBeftp:\fR construct is obsolete.
